      "instructions": "Rub roast with 2 tablespoons olive oil all over.In a small mixing bowl combine chili powder and next 6 ingredients and sprinkle evenly over entire roast.Arrange onion in the bottom of a crock pot or slow cooker and place seasoned roast on top. Add garlic, water and vinegar.Cook on low for 8-9 hours until tender and begins to fall apart easily.Remove from crock pot and using two forks pull on opposing sides to shred. Taste and adjust salt and pepper seasoning if needed.In a small mixing bowl add sour cream, avocados, lime juice and salt and pepper and mash to blend well.Layer shredded beef in tortillas followed by shredded cheese and next 6 ingredients (as desired).Top with avocado crema and serve.",
