      "instructions": "Directions:In a large saucepan or dutch oven, heat olive oil over medium heat. Sautéed onions and garlic about 5 minutes or until soft and beginning to caramelize.Add tomatoes, purée and roasted tomatoes; stirring and breaking up with a wooden spoon. Bring to a simmer and allow to cook for about 5 minutes.Stir in oregano, basil, salt, pepper and wine. Lower heat and simmer for 15 minutes or until sauce is slightly reduced.Blend with an immersion blender to achieve the desired consistency. I like a chunky-ish sauce, so left mine with a bit of chunk in it.Sauce can be kept in air tight containers in the refrigerator for up to 4 days.",
