      "instructions": "Line a 8x8 baking dish with parchment paper.In a microwavable bowl, sift the powdered sugar and cocoa powder. Add a pinch of salt and mix.Add milk and vanilla extract and using a wooden spoon mix everything together. You'll have big lumps and still some of the powdered sugar and cocoa will be dry but don't worry, that's ok.Add the butter on top, just a big chunk right out of the fridge, doesn't need to be melted. Place the bowl in the microwave oven and microwave on high for 2 minutes.Remove from microwave and using the same wooden spoon mix it all together until smooth. When you first take it out of the microwave, you might still see a big chunk of butter, but that's ok, keep on stirring and the butter will melt. You'll notice as you're stirring the mixture if thickening. Add in the pecans and stir.Pour the fudge in the prepared baking dish and spread it evenly. Sprinkle with fleur de sel.Refrigerate for at least an hour or until it sets.Cut into pieces and serve.",
