      "instructions": "In a medium sauce pan, off heat, add sugar, cocoa powder, corn starch and salt. Whisk to combine or sift together.Add Horizon Organic Whole Milk and whisk to combine, then add Horizon Organic Heavy Whipping Cream and whisk again to make sure there are no lumps.Place on burner over medium to medium high and bring to boil. Once it starts to boil, lower heat to medium and cook one minute, stirring continually. Remove from heat.Stir in vanilla and Horizon Organic Unsalted Butter and grated chocolate. Cover and let sit five minutes covered then stir again. Spoon into four 8-ounce serving bowls.**If pudding will not be served right away, cover each cup with plastic, pressing plastic right down onto the surface of the pudding to prevent a skin from forming.While pudding cools, whip Horizon Organic Heavy Whipping Cream in a cold bowl with a whisk until stiff peaks form. Spoon into a pastry bag with a star tip for a decorative top. Serve whipped cream over pudding. Sprinkle with colorful sprinkles if desired.",
