      "instructions": "Into a medium bowl add HALF of parsley and oregano, all of rosemary, thyme, half garlic and 2 tablespoons olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Pour HALF the marinade over skirt steak reserving the remaining. Set aside to marinate at room temperature for at least 10 minutes. Into a separate medium bowl, whisk together remaining parsley, oregano and garlic, mayonnaise, white wine vinegar and 2 tablespoons olive oil. Season with salt/pepper. Set aside. Rinse radicchio and pat dry. Halve lengthwise (keeping roots intact). Cut each half in thirds. Add 1 tablespoon olive oil and radicchio to a grill pan over medium heat. Cook until charred and wilted, approximately 4 minutes, flipping half way through. Set aside. Add steak to pan and cook until browned on outside and medium rare, approximately 3 minutes per side. Remove from pan and allow to rest for approximately 5 minutes. Cut against the grain into slices.Divide steak and radicchio evenly between 2 plates. Drizzle dressing over radicchio and reserved marinade over steak.",
